  "text": "Regarding the inverse association with n À 6 intake observed in this study, this finding is consistent with a decreased risk of EOC with a high n À 6 intake in an Australian case-control study; this study further evaluated the food sources of n À 6 and concluded that the inverse association was due to selected food sources (e.g., avocado, vegetables (not potatoes) and nuts) but not n À 6 intake itself [CITATION_1] ). In the current study, the top two food contributors to n À 6 were mayonnaise (11%) and chicken without skin (8%); hence the potential mechanisms that may explain the inverse association with n À 6 in this study are uncertain. As most previous prospective studies have examined polyunsaturated fat Abbreviations: CI ¼ confidence interval; EOC ¼ epithelial ovarian cancer; MA ¼ Massachusetts; N (cases) ¼ number of cases; n À 3 ¼ omega-3; n À 6 ¼ omega-6; NH ¼ New Hampshire; OC ¼ oral contraceptive; OR ¼ odds ratio; Q1, Q4 ¼ quartiles 1, 4.",
